Evercore Hires Tim Main as Senior Adviser for Financial Services

-- B y   L a u r a   M a r c i n e k
-- 
2011-10-03T13:00:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/evercore-hires-tim-main-as-senior-adviser-for-financial-services.html
Evercore Partners Inc. (EVR) , the
investment bank founded by former deputy U.S. Treasury secretary
Roger Altman, hired Tim Main as a senior adviser to focus on
financial-services clients.  Main spent 23 years at  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM)  and recently
ran the bank’s North American Financial Institutions group and
was co-head of the global unit, New York-based Evercore said
today in a statement. He will be based in New York.  Evercore has advised on $95.3 billion in announced
transactions this year, ranking it 12th on the M&A league
tables, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  “Tim is a highly regarded adviser to large, multinational
financial services companies and has a stellar track record,
helping to build a leading FIG franchise at his previous firm,”
Altman, 65, said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Marcinek in  New York  at 
